      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BUTTER CUP (8) has recorded two wins and three minor placings from the past five starts. Added to her reputation at her latest appearance when she got the job done by 3.5 metres over 1660m at this track. Won't spend a penny from this draw but luck may play a role on the bell lap. That latest effort is good enough to take out a race like this. JEWEL MISTRESS (9) settled in the leading division but couldn't finish the race off and could only manage sixth last start over 1730m at Bathurst, that effort coming after a minor placing at Bathurst the run before. Hard to know where she gets from this slightly awkward draw. Has the class to take this out. VIOLET JAY (7) is in the mix following a respectable second at her most recent appearance over 1660m at this track. CHILLAX (4) is the next elect off a last-start win by 3 metres at this track over 1660m.",
